records.addlTxt:
08:43 AM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Jacob L Valdes-Lukasik in court.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Julian Marrufo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court inquires if the defendant plans to retain counsel.  Defendant advises he plans to proceed pro se.  Court inquires if there is an offer and how the defendant plans to proceed.  Defendant advises he would like to accept the offer and resolve the matter.  Court provides the defendant with the appropriate documents to resolve the matter today.  Court takes a break at 8:46 a.m.  Case recalled at 9:18 a.m.; all appearances remain the same.  Court has the completed waiver of right to attorney form and plea questionnaire from the defendant and will proceed with plea and sentencing today.  Court first has colloquy with the defendant regarding his waiver of right to counsel.  Court finds the defendant is knowingly, voluntarily, and intelligently waiving his right to counsel.  State recites the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1, Court finds defendant guilty.

Sentencng arguments made by the State.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1:
The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld sentence (2 Days Credit - to be held and used IF the defenant is revoked and sentenced.)

Term of Probation: 1 Year - Court will allow for early termination after 6 Months if approved by the Agent.

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	No contact with the Victim listed in the Criminal Complaint.
-	AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs;
-	No Use or Possession of CBD products;
-	No use or possession of any controlled substances without a valid doctors prescription
-	No use of possession of vaping products;
-	Sign Medical Release for Agent;

FINE or COSTS:  Waived by the Court.

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.
